                            <comment id="217083" author="adilger" created="Fri, 22 Dec 2017 10:03:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Close old bug that has not been seen in a long time.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="64960" author="adilger" created="Fri, 23 Aug 2013 16:21:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is an acceptable failure condition, if one of the OSTs is full, or if it is slow and has run out of precreated objects.  It might relate to the &quot;OST full&quot; problem in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3633&quot; title=&quot;sanity.sh test_101d failed for &amp;#39;dd failed&amp;#39;&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-3633&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-3633&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but I&apos;m currently unable to bring up the maloo results.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The test should be fixed to verify the stripe count to be at least:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;        [ $stripe_count -ge $((STRIPE_COUNT * 3 / 4 + 1)) ]
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
